The Gallican Churches, to which this festival was un- known, had another of the same significance, at least in regard to the discovery of the true cross. They celebrated it on the 3rd of May. It is found on this date in several early manuscripts of the Hieronymian Martyr- ology.2 In the two Gallican Sacramentaries of Autun (Missale Gothicum) and Bobbio respectively it appears between the octave of Easter and the Rogation days, without a more precise indication of date.
